quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  43,1,Hā Mīm
  43,2,By the clear Book
  43,3,"Indeed, We have made it an Arabic Qur’an so that you may understand"
  43,4,"and it is in the Master Book [Preserved Tablet] with us, highly esteemed, full of wisdom"
  43,5,Should We then turn the Reminder away from you simply because you are a transgressing people
  43,6,How many a prophet did We send to the earlier peoples
  43,7,No prophet ever came to them except that they ridiculed him
  43,8,"So We destroyed them, although they were greater in might than these [Pagans], and the stories of the earlier nations have already been related"
  43,9,"If you ask them, “who created the heavens and earth?”, they will surely say, “The All-Mighty, the All-Knowing created them.”"
  43,10,"It is He Who spread out the earth for you, and made therein pathways for you, so that you may find your way"
  43,11,"And it is He Who sends down rain from the sky in due measure, by which We revive dead land. This is how you will be brought forth [from the grave]"
  43,12,"And it is He Who created all types of things, and made for you ships and animals on which you ride"
  43,13,"so that you may settle yourselves on their backs, then remember the blessings of your Lord when you have settled thereupon and say, “Glory be to Him Who has subjected this for us, for we could not have done it by ourselves"
  43,14,It is to our Lord that we will surely return.”
  43,15,"Yet they ascribe to Him some of His slaves as offspring. Indeed, man is clearly ungrateful"